&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Shore Skin Center&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Plymouth Massachusetts&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;is looking for a strong dermatologist to join our well established &amp;amp; highly regarded practice with a large &amp;amp; loyal patient base.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Opportunity Highlights:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly Competitive Compensation: $650,000+ realistic potential (Salary + Productivity Bonus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Immediate patient volume from 30+ patients per day at your comfort level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Established referral network and loyal patient population&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent support staff and streamlined workflows: 2-3 MAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible practice mix: medical, surgical, and cosmetic dermatology&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A team-based approach with strong support from in-office dermatology colleagues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Physician-led organization with long-term stability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;EMA Charting system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About the Community:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Living in Plymouth, Massachusetts, offers a laid-back blend of history, coastal living, and a friendly community atmosphere. With its roots tracing back to the Mayflower landing, Plymouth retains a sense of historical charm seen in landmarks like Plymouth Rock and the Plimoth Plantation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The coastal setting adds a relaxing touch to daily life, with serene views of the Atlantic Ocean and leisurely waterfront activities. Local seafood eateries contribute to a calm and easygoing lifestyle, perfect for those seeking a quieter pace.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Plymouth&#39;s community spirit is evident in its small-town vibe, where neighbors know each other, and local events provide a chance to connect. Whether exploring historic sites or enjoying the coastal scenery, living in Plymouth offers a relaxed and welcoming environment for those appreciating a more laid-back way of life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;About Northeast Dermatology Associates:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a patient-centered dermatology practice committed to providing the highest-quality care for patients of all ages, including medical, surgical, cosmetic, and pathology services. Our well established practice has built a tremendous and loyal following of patients resulting in an unmet demand for Dermatologic services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Who is PhyNet Dermatology?&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PhyNet Dermatology is a network of dermatologists, dermatopathologists and MOHS surgeons supported by experienced healthcare leaders who serve as a comprehensive practice partner to enable physicians to do what they do best: provide quality medical care and an outstanding patient experience.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;South Shore Skin Center is seeking an &lt;strong&gt;experienced Dermatology Nurse Practitioner&lt;/strong&gt; to join our well-established practice serving a loyal patient base in Norwell, MA. This is a weekend-focused position, perfect for an NP seeking a flexible 2–3 day/week schedule.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide high-quality medical dermatology care for patients of all ages&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform skin assessments, diagnose conditions, and develop treatment plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct minor procedures and assist with dermatologic surgeries as appropriate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with physicians and support staff to ensure excellent patient outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize EMA electronic health record system for charting and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate patients on skin health, treatment plans, and preventive care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive compensation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Weekend schedule (2–3 days/week)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong patient volumes through a local referral network&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support staff including MAs trained to scribe, manage prior authorizations, and provide patient follow-up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern, fully equipped facilities with specialized equipment and procedure rooms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work in a patient-centered, collaborative environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Norwell, MA:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Norwell is a scenic, family-friendly town on the South Shore known for its excellent schools, beautiful parks, and safe, welcoming community. It offers a peaceful suburban lifestyle while providing convenient access to Boston and coastal recreation. Residents enjoy local shops, restaurants, and a variety of outdoor activities, making it a great place to live and work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current Nurse Practitioner license in Massachusetts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dermatology experience preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong clinical assessment and procedural skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and patient education abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work independently and as part of a collaborative healthcare team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mohs Medical Assistant/Surgical Technician plays a crucial role in delivering high-quality, patient-centered care to individuals undergoing Mohs surgery. This position ensures the maintenance of a safe, efficient, and quality-focused environment by conducting pre-surgical evaluations, providing patient and family education, assisting with surgical procedures, managing patient flow, and maintaining meticulous patient records in both electronic and physical formats.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pay and Hours:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay range is $25 -$27 hourly, Hours are Monday - Thursday, 10 hours daily.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To perform effectively in this role, the candidate must fulfill the following duties with or without reasonable accommodations:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct initial assessments and review health survey data to develop comprehensive care plans tailored to patient needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide detailed pre-operative and post-operative education to patients and their families, ensuring understanding and compliance with care instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare the surgical area by organizing necessary instruments, equipment, and anesthesia.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the surgeon during procedures, including scrubbing in, handing instruments, cutting sutures, and maintaining a sterile operative field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the surgical environment remains clean, organized, and compliant with established protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer anesthesia under the direct supervision of the physician, ensuring accurate dosages and adherence to proper techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accurately document all aspects of patient care, including detailed notes for each Mohs procedure within the Electronic Medical Records (EMR) system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain comprehensive and accurate records of follow-up communications and post-operative instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement practices that promote excellence in surgical care and patient outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a sterile environment by strictly adhering to safety standards and protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor patient safety during procedures and recovery, taking all necessary precautions to ensure their well-being.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear, written post-operative instructions, ensuring patients have access to an effective communication system for follow-up questions or concerns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist patients with mobility following surgery to ensure safety and prevent falls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate and maintain surgical equipment, including the autoclave, ensuring all instruments are properly sterilized and ready for use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Knowledge, Skills, &amp;amp; Abilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma or GED required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of 2 years of experience as a medical assistant or surgical technician; experience in dermatology is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with Electronic Medical Records (EMR) systems and Microsoft Office applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in the use of surgical instruments and maintaining sterile environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role requires a proactive, dependable, and detail-oriented individual with the ability to manage multiple tasks in a dynamic healthcare environment. The ideal candidate demonstrates a strong commitment to patient care and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
